Amazon DE2 Coding Pattern
The interviewer is often looking for:
Step 1
Can you solve it?
Step 2
Can you optimize?
Example:
Brute Force -> O(n²)HashMap -> O(n)
Step 3
Can you discuss edge cases?
Example:


Empty input


Null input


Duplicates


Very large input


Step 4
Can you explain complexity?
Always finish with:
Time Complexity = O(...)Space Complexity = O(...)
For your Amazon DE2 interview, I would spend 70% of coding prep on HashMap + Sliding Window + Frequency counting problems, because that is where most DE coding rounds tend to live.